{#-
Renders the `design-author-update` YAML payload as a
human-readable markdown report for the `design-review-update`
human gate.

Caller (the `render-design-update` Python tool) is expected
to pre-group `change_plan.files[]` by `action` and pass them
as `files_created`, `files_modified`, `files_deleted` so the
template stays declarative.

Required variables (StrictUndefined — all must be provided,
empty list / empty string are fine):

  skill.name              str
  skill.namespace         str
  skill.type              str
  skill.path              str
  change_request          str  (user's free-form description)
  files_created           list[{path, summary, rationale?}]
  files_modified          list[{path, summary, rationale?}]
  files_deleted           list[{path, summary, rationale?}]
  open_questions          list[str]
  rationale               str
  canonical_yaml_path     str  (for the footer pointer)
-#}
# Update: `{{ skill.name }}` ({{ skill.type }})

> Skill at `{{ skill.path }}` (namespace: `{{ skill.namespace }}`)

## Change request

{{ change_request | trim }}

{% macro file_block(files, heading, empty_msg) -%}
### {{ heading }}

{% if files -%}
{% for f in files -%}
- **`{{ f.path }}`** — {{ f.summary | trim | replace('\n', ' ') }}
{%- if 'rationale' in f and f.rationale %}
  _{{ f.rationale | trim | replace('\n', ' ') }}_
{%- endif %}
{% endfor -%}
{% else -%}
_{{ empty_msg }}_
{%- endif %}
{%- endmacro %}

## Files affected

{{ file_block(files_created,  'Created',  'No new files.') }}
{{ file_block(files_modified, 'Modified', 'No edits to existing files.') }}
{{ file_block(files_deleted,  'Deleted',  'No removals.') }}

{% if open_questions -%}
## Open questions

The author wants confirmation on the following before
materialization. Address each in your review feedback if you
choose `revise`.

{% for q in open_questions -%}
- {{ q | trim | replace('\n', ' ') }}
{% endfor %}
{%- endif %}

{% if rationale | trim -%}
## Rationale

{{ rationale | trim }}
{%- endif %}

---

The canonical edit target is the design YAML at
`{{ canonical_yaml_path }}`. Edits round-trip through the
review gate — `accept` copies the (possibly hand-tweaked)
YAML into the gate output; `revise` loops back to
`design-author-update` with your free-text feedback.
